<2ND_LINE>AM-People-Bernsen,0216</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>`L.A. Law' Star Corbin Bernsen Marries British Actress Amanda Pays</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Corbin Bernsen, who plays the shrewd divorce
lawyer on ``L.A. Law,'' married British actress Amanda Pays of ``Max
Headroom'' fame in a private ceremony Saturday, a publicist said.
   Bernsen, 34, the silk-suited Arnie Becker on NBC-TV's hit series,
exchanged vows with Miss Pays, 29, at a lodge in suburban Los
Angeles as about 170 guests watched, spokeswoman Marilyn Heston said.
   The couple, who are expecting their first child in March, lived
together for about a year, Ms. Heston said.
   The bride wore blue velvet while the groom sported a blue blazer
and slacks.
   ``It's a very '40s look,'' Ms. Heston said. ``And there are a lot
of smiles all around, with guests on the bride's side from as far
away as England and France.''
   With ``L.A. Law'' still in production, the couple's honeymoon
plans are on hold for several weeks, she said.
   Miss Pays, whose film credits include ``Oxford Blues,'' will
appear in the film ``Leviathan,'' scheduled for a March release.
   Bernsen has made three films scheduled for release in 1989,
including one titled ``Major League,'' co-starring Charlie Sheen and
Tom Berenger.
   The couple will reside at Bernsen's Hollywood Hills home.
</TEXT>
