hurling charges of violations at each other.
   Pakistan's foreign minister, Sahabzada Yaqub Khan, said
Afghan-Soviet aircraft have intruded into Pakistan airspace 104
times since the accord signing. He made these allegations in a
letter sent to the U.N. security council. The news agency published
the text of the letter.
   The letter alleged the violations left 134 people dead.
