<HEAD>Woman Finds Missing Son's Body In Closet</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A woman trying to find the source of a strange
odor in her house opened a closet door and found the body of her
18-year-old son, who was last seen on Halloween, police said Sunday.
   Joseph Gooch had alcohol problems and had been treated
periodically for mental problems, said Detective Nick Gaudio.
   An autopsy was being performed to determine how long the man had
been dead and how he died, Gaudio said.
   Patricia Gooch, 59, told police her son might have been using
drugs.
   ``We have no reason to suspect that he has been killed,'' Gaudio
said, noting that Gooch ``was known to hide in various places in the
house.''
