<2ND_LINE>AM-Chinese Espionage,0276</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Authorities Say China's Spies Most Active In United States</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The FBI says Chinese spies are active in
California, home to 25 percent of the nation's defense contracts,
but a Chinese official says the conclusion is based on ignorance.
   ``As far as human intelligence collection, the Chinese have now
outstripped the Soviets in California. Because of the political
climate, they have more opportunities here and appear to be
utilizing them,'' said Harry J. Godfrey III, head of FBI
counterintelligence in Los Angeles.
   About 400,000 people of Chinese descent live in California. There
are about 100 Chinese government-owned companies in the state, an
80-member consulate in San Francisco and a 30-member consulate in
Los Angeles.
   ``We know they are running operations here,'' Godfrey said. ``We
have seen cases where they have encouraged people to apply to the
CIA, the FBI, Naval Investigative Service and other defense
agencies. They have also attempted to recruit people at our research
facilities at Los Alamos (National Laboratory in New Mexico) and at
Lawrence Livermore.''
   ``We don't have intelligence ties,'' said Zhang Pengxiang,
China's political consul in Los Angeles. ``It's really imagination.
Not only that, it's ignorance. They really don't know China. We are
open here. Quite open.''
   Ma Yuzhen, China's consul general in Los Angeles, also denied
espionage efforts.
   ``I think that is the most inaccurate view of Chinese activity
here. None of us here are involved in intelligence gathering. No
Chinese consular officer is ever doing such things,'' Yuzhen said.
   China is the world's fifth largest arms merchant, selling more
than $2 billion worth of weapons annually.
</TEXT>
