confirm the report.
   In Jastrzebie, about 1,000 people marched from a Catholic church
to a former Solidarity headquarters building and listened to
speeches by regional Solidarity leaders, said group spokesman Robert
Kozak. There was no police intervention, he said.
   Strikes by miners in Jastrzebie in mid-August touched off
Poland's worst labor unrest in seven years.
